WhosevoicesIdesirealoudwithmine:
Hail,KingofScotland!
Hail,KingofScotland!
Weshallnotspendalargeexpenseoftime
Beforewereckonwithyourseveralloves,
Andmakeusevenwithyou.Mythanesandkinsmen,
Henceforthbeearls,thefirstthateverScotland
Insuchanhonournamed.What'smoretodo,
Whichwouldbeplantednewlywiththetime,
Ascallinghomeourexiledfriendsabroad
Thatfledthesnaresofwatchfultyranny;
Producingforththecruelministers
Ofthisdeadbutcherandhisfiend-likequeen,
Who,as'tisthought,byselfandviolenthands
Tookoffherlife;this,andwhatneedfulelse
Thatcallsuponus,bythegraceofGrace,
Wewillperforminmeasure,timeandplace:
So,thankstoallatonceandtoeachone,
Whomweinvitetoseeuscrown'datScone.
